---
/* SystemMap.astro — APM system architecture map for the honeywell-apm case study.
   Vertical flow chart: Physical → Event → Incident → Response → Health → Dashboard.
   Uses map-* component classes from globals.css. Zero inline styles except dynamic values. */
---

<div class="flex flex-col gap-0 max-w-3xl">

  {/* ── Layer 1: Physical ── */}
  <div class="map-layer" data-animate>
    <span class="type-label">Physical Layer</span>
    <p class="type-body leading-relaxed">
      Everything starts with a physical asset. K-101 is a centrifugal compressor
      classified as Safety-critical. It has sub-assets, and each sub-asset has
      sensors with thresholds.
    </p>

    <div class="map-node map-node--highlight">
      <span class="type-label">Asset</span>
      <span class="type-body font-bold">K-101 -- Centrifugal Compressor</span>
      <span class="type-meta">Criticality: <code>A (Safety)</code> · Production Weight: <code>0.20</code></span>
    </div>

    <div class="map-node-row">
      <div class="map-node">
        <span class="type-label">Sub-asset</span>
        <span class="type-body font-bold">Drive End Bearing</span>
        <span class="type-meta">Vibration: <code>7.8 mm/s</code> (threshold: <code>7.1</code>)</span>
        <span class="type-meta">Temperature: <code>108 C</code> (threshold: <code>95</code>)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="map-node">
        <span class="type-label">Sub-asset</span>
        <span class="type-body font-bold">Lube Oil System</span>
        <span class="type-meta">Oil Pressure: <code>1.0 bar</code> (threshold: <code>1.5</code>)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="map-node">
        <span class="type-label">Sub-asset</span>
        <span class="type-body font-bold">Anti-Surge</span>
        <span class="type-meta">Surge Margin: <code>7%</code> (threshold: <code>10%</code>)</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="map-connector" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  {/* ── Layer 2: Event ── */}
  <div class="map-layer" data-animate>
    <span class="type-label">Event Layer</span>
    <p class="type-body leading-relaxed">
      When a sensor value crosses its threshold, the system creates an event.
      The severity is computed, not assigned -- it comes from a matrix of what
      happened crossed with how critical the asset is. Every event carries
      structured metadata: cause, consequence, and recommendation, each tracked
      with its source (human or system), confidence level, and confirmation status.
    </p>

    <div class="map-node map-node--highlight">
      <span class="type-label">Event</span>
      <span class="type-body font-bold">EVT-005 -- High Vibration Trip</span>
      <span class="type-meta">eventType: <code>trip</code> · Asset: <code>K-101 (A Safety)</code></span>
      <span class="type-meta">Severity derivation: <code>trip</code> x <code>A (Safety)</code> = <code>Critical</code></span>
    </div>

    {/* Severity matrix */}
    <div class="map-node">
      <span class="type-label">Severity Matrix</span>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th class="type-meta font-bold text-left p-2"></th>
              <th class="type-meta font-bold text-left p-2">A (Safety)</th>
              <th class="type-meta font-bold text-left p-2">B (Production)</th>
              <th class="type-meta font-bold text-left p-2">C (Support)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="type-meta font-bold p-2">trip</td>
              <td class="p-2"><code>Critical</code></td>
              <td class="p-2"><code>High</code></td>
              <td class="p-2"><code>Medium</code></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="type-meta font-bold p-2">alarm</td>
              <td class="p-2"><code>High</code></td>
              <td class="p-2"><code>Medium</code></td>
              <td class="p-2"><code>Low</code></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="type-meta font-bold p-2">alert</td>
              <td class="p-2"><code>Medium</code></td>
              <td class="p-2"><code>Low</code></td>
              <td class="p-2"><code>Low</code></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="map-node">
      <span class="type-label">Event Metadata</span>
      <span class="type-meta">Cause: bearing wear from oil starvation</span>
      <span class="type-meta">Consequence: compressor trip, production loss</span>
      <span class="type-meta">Recommendation: inspect bearing, flush lube oil</span>
      <span class="type-meta mt-2">Status lifecycle: <code>new</code> → <code>in-progress</code> → <code>closed</code></span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="map-connector" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  {/* ── Layer 3: Incident + Narrative ── */}
  <div class="map-layer" data-animate>
    <span class="type-label">Incident + Narrative Layer</span>
    <p class="type-body leading-relaxed">
      The system correlates events by asset, timing, and causal chain. An engineer
      confirms the grouping and identifies the root cause. This turns scattered alerts
      into a single incident with a clear story. The dashboard surfaces that story as
      a three-act narrative: what triggered it, what it caused, and what confirmed it.
    </p>

    <div class="map-node map-node--highlight">
      <span class="type-label">Incident</span>
      <span class="type-body font-bold">INC-001 -- K-101 Bearing Failure</span>
      <span class="type-meta"><code>7</code> events · Status: <code>investigating</code></span>
    </div>

    <div class="map-node-row">
      <div class="map-node">
        <span class="type-label">Trigger</span>
        <span class="type-body font-bold">EVT-002</span>
        <span class="type-meta">Oil pressure drop (first signal)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="map-node">
        <span class="type-label">Consequence</span>
        <span class="type-body font-bold">EVT-005</span>
        <span class="type-meta">High vibration trip (the failure)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="map-node">
        <span class="type-label">Confirmation</span>
        <span class="type-body font-bold">EVT-011</span>
        <span class="type-meta">Manual inspection (bearing damage confirmed)</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="map-connector" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  {/* ── Layer 4: Response ── */}
  <div class="map-layer" data-animate>
    <span class="type-label">Response Layer</span>
    <p class="type-body leading-relaxed">
      Events spawn work orders and investigations. Work orders fix the problem.
      Investigations understand it. An investigation can span multiple events and
      reach back into history.
    </p>

    <div class="map-node-row">
      <div class="map-node">
        <span class="type-label">Work Orders</span>
        <span class="type-body font-bold">WO-4481</span>
        <span class="type-meta">Bearing inspection · Urgency: <code>Emergency</code></span>
        <span class="type-body font-bold mt-2">WO-4482</span>
        <span class="type-meta">Oil flush · Urgency: <code>Emergency</code></span>
      </div>
      <div class="map-node">
        <span class="type-label">Investigation</span>
        <span class="type-body font-bold">IN-0891</span>
        <span class="type-meta">Root cause analysis · Status: <code>Investigating</code></span>
        <span class="type-meta">Spans <code>5</code> events · References historical events</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="map-connector" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  {/* ── Layer 5: Health ── */}
  <div class="map-layer" data-animate>
    <span class="type-label">Health Layer</span>
    <p class="type-body leading-relaxed">
      All of this activity flows into the health metrics. OEE breaks down into
      availability, performance, and quality. MTBF, MTTR, and RUL tell the
      reliability story. Every number derives from the events and work orders above.
    </p>

    <div class="map-node-row">
      <div class="map-node map-node--highlight">
        <span class="type-label">Asset Health</span>
        <span class="type-body font-bold">K-101</span>
        <span class="type-meta">OEE: <code>64.2%</code></span>
        <span class="type-meta">Availability: derived from trips x MTTR</span>
        <span class="type-meta">Performance: <code>0.649</code> (MES in production)</span>
        <span class="type-meta">Quality: <code>0.990</code> (MES in production)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="map-node">
        <span class="type-label">Reliability</span>
        <span class="type-meta">MTBF: derived from trip count</span>
        <span class="type-meta">MTTR: derived from WO completion times</span>
        <span class="type-meta">RUL: <code>5 days</code> (projected from trend)</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="map-node-row">
      <div class="map-node">
        <span class="type-label">Plant Health</span>
        <span class="type-meta">OEE: <code>76.3%</code> (weighted average)</span>
        <span class="type-meta">Availability: <code>78.4%</code></span>
        <span class="type-meta">Performance: <code>93.8%</code></span>
        <span class="type-meta">Quality: <code>99.1%</code></span>
      </div>
      <div class="map-node">
        <span class="type-label">Thresholds</span>
        <span class="type-meta">OEE: warning <code>&lt; 85%</code> / critical <code>&lt; 75%</code></span>
        <span class="type-meta">Availability: warning <code>&lt; 90%</code> / critical <code>&lt; 80%</code></span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="map-connector" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  {/* ── Layer 6: Dashboard ── */}
  <div class="map-layer" data-animate>
    <span class="type-label">Dashboard Layer</span>
    <p class="type-body leading-relaxed">
      The engineer sees all of this at 7 AM, ordered by the morning triage
      workflow: check health, understand cause, check response, identify remaining
      work, then drill into specifics.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-3">
      <div class="map-node">
        <span class="type-body font-bold">1. System Health</span>
        <span class="type-meta">"is something wrong?"</span>
      </div>
      <div class="map-node">
        <span class="type-body font-bold">2. What Happened</span>
        <span class="type-meta">"what caused it?"</span>
      </div>
      <div class="map-node">
        <span class="type-body font-bold">3. In Progress</span>
        <span class="type-meta">"is anyone on it?"</span>
      </div>
      <div class="map-node">
        <span class="type-body font-bold">4. Needs Action</span>
        <span class="type-meta">"what still needs me?"</span>
      </div>
      <div class="map-node">
        <span class="type-body font-bold">5. Assets</span>
        <span class="type-meta">"show me everything"</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>
